com.amazon.device.associates
Interface ShoppingListener

public interface ShoppingListener

You must create a class implementing the ShoppingListener and register an instance of this class with ShoppingService.setListener(ShoppingListener) before using other APIs in the ShoppingService.

The ShoppingService API follows a request and response pattern. The requests are initiated via ShoppingService methods and the responses are delivered through callbacks implemented as part of ShoppingListener.

For example, when you initiate a purchase by calling ShoppingService.purchase(PurchaseRequest), you will receive onPurchaseResponse(PurchaseResponse) callback.

Please be aware that the callbacks you implement will be invoked in the UI thread. This is designed to simplify handling events and updating UI controls. Any CPU intensive or time consuming task should be executed in a separate thread using an AsyncTask.

For all ShoppingService requests, the corresponding ShoppingListener response callback is guaranteed to be invoked. However in case like network failure, the response might be delayed.

onServiceStatusResponse

void onServiceStatusResponse(ServiceStatusResponse response)
This callback method is invoked in response to ShoppingService.getServiceStatus() and delivers ServiceStatusResponse object. You can use ServiceStatusResponse to retrieve API capability information.

Parameters:
response - A ServiceStatusResponse object.

onPurchaseResponse

void onPurchaseResponse(PurchaseResponse response)

This callback method is invoked in response to ShoppingService.purchase(PurchaseRequest). The callback signifies completion of the purchase flow.

The PurchaseResponse.getStatus() returns SUCCESSFUL if receiveReceipt was set to true in PurchaseRequest and the user completes a successful purchase or if receiveReceipt was set to false and product detail page was successfully displayed to the user. The PurchaseResponse.getStatus() returns INVALID_ID if an invalid product ID was passed in the request to ShoppingService.purchase(com.amazon.device.associates.PurchaseRequest).

Parameters:
response - A PurchaseResponse object. Use PurchaseResponse object to confirm if a valid productID was passed to ShoppingService.purchase(PurchaseRequest) method.

onReceiptsResponse

void onReceiptsResponse(ReceiptsResponse response)

This callback method is invoked in response to ShoppingService.getReceipts(ReceiptsRequest) and delivers ReceiptsResponse object. Retrieve purchase receipts using ReceiptsResponse.getReceipts(). Make sure you check if the receipts are available or if the request was successful using ReceiptsResponse.getStatus().

Receipts will be returned for the purchases completed in the current app made by the currently logged in user. Receipts will only be returned for purchases for which receiveReceipt was set to true in PurchaseRequest.

Parameters:
response - A ReceiptsResponse object. Use response object to retrieve receipts.

onSearchResponse

void onSearchResponse(SearchResponse response)

This callback method is invoked in response to ShoppingService.search(SearchRequest) and delivers SearchResponse object. Retrieve product information using SearchResponse.getProducts().

The search results are returned in a paginated fashion. Use SearchResponse.getPage() to get the current page number. You can also create SearchRequest for the next page and call ShoppingService.search(SearchRequest) to retrieve the next page. Check the current page number against total pages before initiating request for the next page. You can get total pages using SearchResponse.getTotalPages().

You should also confirm that the search request was successful using SearchByIdResponse.getStatus().

Parameters:
response - A SearchResponse object. Use response object to retrieve search results.

onSearchByIdResponse

void onSearchByIdResponse(SearchByIdResponse response)

This callback method is invoked in response to ShoppingService.searchById(SearchByIdRequest) and delivers SearchByIdResponse object. Retrieve product information using SearchByIdResponse.getProducts(). Make sure you check for products that are unavailable using SearchByIdResponse.getUnavailableProductIds(). Also confirm that the search request was successful using SearchByIdResponse.getStatus().

Parameters:
response - A SearchByIdResponse object. Use response object to retrieve search results.
